 | in my 74 Westy, I just noticed today that the gas pedal appears not right.
 |  It appears that it is just connected at the bottom right and the bottom
 | left appears just loose.  As a consequence, the gas pedal leans to the
 | left, almost underneath the brake pedal.
 | 
 | Is there some sort of bracket that holds the gas pedal at the bottom?  How
 | do I go about hooking it back up and returning it to normal?


Rust, as in you don't have any place for
the pedal to hang onto.  My solution, 
admittedly non-stock, is to screw a large
longtailed hinge go the floor and to the 
pedal and just live with it.  It beats
driving home at an idle, which, of course,
I got to do when first this broke.

